@startuml
title Sequence Diagram: Interact with an Art Piece

actor User
participant "ControllerInput Manager" as Input
participant "HUD" as HUD
participant "Room Manager" as Room
participant "Canvas (PaintableSurfaceRT)" as Canvas
participant "SupabaseArtworkRepository" as ArtworkRepo
participant "Supabase SDK" as SDK
participant "Network Manager" as Network
participant "Event Logger" as Logger

database "Supabase Storage" as Storage
database "Supabase Database" as DB

== Proximity Detection ==
User -> Input: Walks up to an art piece (threshold reached)
Input -> Room: Notifies proximity event
Room -> HUD: Highlight nearby art piece
HUD -> User: Art piece highlighted — interaction mode available

== Art Piece Selection ==
User -> Input: Selects the highlighted art piece
Input -> Room: Confirm art piece selection
Room -> ArtworkRepo: GetArtworkPaths(artworkId)
activate ArtworkRepo
ArtworkRepo -> SDK: Query artworks WHERE id = artworkId
SDK -> DB: SELECT image_url, thumbnail_url FROM artwork
DB --> SDK: Artwork metadata
SDK --> ArtworkRepo: Return path metadata
ArtworkRepo --> Room: Return (image_url, thumbnail_url)
deactivate ArtworkRepo

Room -> SDK: Download texture (image_url)
SDK -> Storage: GET /storage/v1/object/artwork-images
Storage --> SDK: Byte array
SDK --> Room: Texture2D

Room -> Canvas: SetBackground(texture)
activate Canvas
Canvas -> Canvas: Graphics.Blit(texture → RenderTexture, ping-pong)
Canvas --> Room: Success
deactivate Canvas

Canvas -> HUD: Display interaction options (zoom, rotate, info, etc.)
HUD -> User: Shows interaction options

== Interaction ==
User -> Input: Selects an interaction option (e.g. zoom / rotate / show info)
Input -> Canvas: Send chosen command
Canvas -> Room: Update art display according to user action
Room -> HUD: Render visual change or playback multimedia
HUD -> User: Updated art interaction view
Canvas -> Logger: Log user interaction

alt Selection via Controller
    User -> Input: Uses controller pointer to select art piece
    Input -> Room: Confirm art piece selection
    Room -> HUD: Highlight and enter interaction mode
end

alt Network / Storage Failure
    SDK --> Room: Error / timeout
    Room -> HUD: Show error notification "Unable to load art details"
    HUD -> Logger: Log network error
end

alt Exit Interaction Mode
    User -> Input: Exits interaction mode
    Input -> Room: Notify exit event
    Room -> HUD: Revert to free-move mode
    HUD -> User: Normal navigation restored
    Room -> Logger: Log exit interaction
end

note over ArtworkRepo, Storage
    Artwork textures are fetched from Supabase Storage
    and seeded into PaintableSurfaceRT via Graphics.Blit.
    DisplayOnly mode — painting is disabled during viewing.
end note
@enduml
